The paper deals with optimization problems in computer science, specifically the matching problem and the metric traveling salesperson problem. The techniques used involve linear and semidefinite programming, as well as polynomial identities. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.GT (discrete mathematics and combinatorial optimization), and cs.SI (social and information networks).
